HEADWORD: Papaveraceous
<hw>Pa*pav`er*a"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or resembling, a natural family of plants
(<fam>Papaveraceae</fam>) of which the poppy, the celandine, and the
bloodroot are well-known examples.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

